narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Learned a lot about music, and Indonesian culture.
I learned more about my Indonesian heritage and its musical culture, which is something that I've always been interested in.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I thought that it was a strong course that had both textbook reading and instrument playing components, so that we learned about the context of gamelan but also go to experience the music itself.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Amazing course. A must take. Will enhance your Yale experience so much.

Yes, I would definitely take this class! The workload was not too hard: 1 hour of reading with a 200-word reading response every week, 1 take home midterm, and a 3-5 page final essay. With that being said, attendance is really important, and there's a group performance at the end, right around finals period.
